IBM Research Scientists are charting the future of Artificial Intelligence, creating breakthroughs in quantum computing, discovering how blockchain will reshape the enterprise, and much more. Join a team that is dedicated to applying science to some of today's most complex challenges, whether itâ€™s discovering a new way for doctors to help patients, teaming with environmentalists to clean up our waterways or enabling retailers to personalize customer service. 
 
Your Role and Responsibilities 
IBM Research is hiring Research Scientists interesting in solving problems related to but not limited to the following: 
Combining symbolic and reinforcement learning based sequential decision making for solving real world problems at scale 
Modeling real-world problems in AI Planning or a combined reasoning+learning framework and building end-to-end systems 
Creating novel, next generation planning approaches and algorithms 
The mission of our growing group is to bring AI Automation to sequential decision making where we need to identify a few solutions in an immense space of possibilities. Our aim is to address three major challenges: 
Modeling: how to represent, extract, and learn the model 
Theory: formal definition of the computational problems 
Tooling: how to solve computational problems and building end-to-end systems 
Practical applications of our work include Data Science and ML platforms for automated AI pipeline generation, planning for cloud-based modernization of data and applications, planning and resource decision making for large scale Cloud/IT environments. 
 
As part of the IBM Research team, you will conduct world-class research on innovative technologies and solutions and publish in top-tier conferences and journals. 
 
You must be willing to work in Yorktown Heights, NY or Cambridge, MA 
 
Required Technical and Professional Expertise 
 
Demonstrated publication records in top-tier conferences 
Proven knowledge of AI planning and planning tools 
Knowledge of RL algorithms and machine learning frameworks 
Experience using one or more popular programming languages (C/C++, Python, Java, JS, etc.) 
Technical leadership experience. 
Preferred Technical and Professional Expertise 
 
Knowledge of using Natural Language Processing / Natural Language Understanding in a user interaction setting (e.g., for modeling user domains from either documents or user dialogue) 
About Business UnitWith more than 3,000 researchers in 12 labs located across six continents, IBM Research brings together hundreds of researchers who possess unparalleled industry expertise to address some of the world's most challenging problems. Join us as we do pioneering work in areas such as cognitive computing, augmented intelligence, quantum computing, and blockchain, to name a few. 
 
